## The silent failure: swallowed GraphInterrupt

This is the worst class of bug. A node with:

```typescript
try {
  const decision = interrupt("approve?");
  return { approved: decision === "approved" };
} catch (e) {
  console.log("error:", e);   // GraphInterrupt printed and swallowed
  return { approved: false };  // graph silently continues
}
```

Produces: `invoke()` returns `{ approved: false }` with NO `__interrupt__` key, NO error, NO pause. The human approval gate is bypassed silently.

Source: [05-distillation/gotchas/G-009](../05-distillation/gotchas/G-009-swallowed-graph-interrupt.md) | [05-distillation/anti-patterns/AP-002](../05-distillation/anti-patterns/AP-002-try-catch-swallow-interrupt.md)

