## The fix

- Validate `embedding.length === EXPECTED_DIM` client-side before INSERT.
- TypeScript: type the embedding as a fixed-length tuple if practical; or use a runtime assertion:
  ```ts
  function assertDim(v: number[], expected: number): void {
    if (v.length !== expected) {
      throw new Error(`embedding dim mismatch: expected ${expected}, got ${v.length}`);
    }
  }
  ```
- For RPCs accepting `vector(N)` parameter: PostgREST will surface the 22000 as an error response (`status=400`, `error.code='22000'`).
